===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|lien|lang=enm}}, {{term|liggen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|licgan|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|ligjanan|lang=gem-pro}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|legʰ-|lang=ine-pro}}. Cognate with Danish {{term|ligge|lang=en}}, Dutch {{term|liggen|lang=en}}, German {{term|liegen|lang=en}}, Gothic {{term|𐌻𐌹𐌲𐌰𐌽|tr=ligan|lang=got}}, Swedish {{term|ligga|lang=en}}; and with Latin {{term|lectus||bed}}, Irish {{term|luighe|lang=en}}, Russian {{term|лежать|lang=ru}}, Albanian {{term|lagje||inhabited area, neighbourhood|lang=sq}}.

As a noun for {{term|position|lang=en}}, the [[#Noun|noun]] has the same etymology above as the [[#Verb|verb]].

